Rating: 2
I was told by my produce grocer that the early freeze had hurt the chestnut harvest. I substituted almonds instead. It wasn't a great dish, but was good enough that I look forward to trying it again with chestnuts when they become available.

Rating: 4
This was a hit at our Thanksgiving dinner. However, finding good pre-roasted chestnuts can be a problem. Luckily we discovered some dry-packed chestnuts in foil pouches that worked very well. The flavors blended well with other dishes in a traditional Thanksgiving meal.

